cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses new defense techniques for distributed machine learning. It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with breaking Byzantine-tolerant techniques. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with distributed machine learning. It may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses new attack strategies based on inner product manipulation.
